Acacia farnesiana

   [297.jpg]
   Authority (L.) Willd.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
   Synonyms Mimosa farnesiana L., Mimosa acicularis Poir., Acacia
   lenticulata F. Muell., Vachellia farnesiana (L.) Wight & Arn., Acacia
   comosa Gagnep.
   Common names Ellington curse, klu, cassie, espino blanco, aroma,
   popinac, kandaroma, kolu, vaivai vaka-vatona, vaivai vakavotona, ban
   baburi, oki, te kaibakoa (Kiribati), debena (Nauru), mimosa bush,
   needle bush, sweet acacia, Prickly Moses, Perfumed wattle, Cassie
   flower, Sweet Mimosa Bush, Sponge flower, Scented Wattle
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 297

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A thorny bush or small tree up to 1.5-5 m in height
   with large orange-yellow flowers. USES The flowers yield and essential
   oil used in perfumery. The tree also yields a gum, it is used as
   firewood and as an ornamental. GROWING PERIOD Perennial, that begins to
   flower from the 3rd year. COMMON NAMES Huisache, Aromo, Espino blanco,
   Espino ruco, Opoponax, Mimosa bush, Needle bush, Klu, Ellington curse,
   Vaivai vakavotona, Ban baburi, Cassie flower, Cassie, Farnese wattle,
   Mimosa wattle, Sweet acacia. FURTHER INF Scientific synonyms: Mimosa
   acicularis, Vachellia farnesiana. Huisache thrives in dry localities
   and it is drought hardy and fire resistant. Found at elevations between
   sea level and 1300 m. The latitudinal range in Australia is 12-36Â°S.
   Mentioned as a possible agroforestry species. In Fiji it has developed
   into a troublesome weed.

   Sources
